---
/**
 * XR Awards Programme Page
 * URL: /programme
 * Dynamic programme page that fetches event details from database
 */
export const prerender = true;

import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import CTAFooter from '../components/CTAFooter.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import { getR2ImageUrl } from '../utils/r2';
import { supabase } from '../utils/supabase';

// Fetch active event details
const { data: eventDetails } = await supabase
  .from('event_details')
  .select('*')
  .eq('is_active', true)
  .single();

// Get hero image from R2 - using a generic awards/event image
const heroImage = getR2ImageUrl('/images/2025/10/xr-awards-2022-combat-waffle-studios_1760356010976.jpg');

// Calculate reading time based on word count
// Average reading speed: 250 words per minute
const articleContent = `
The XR Awards Programme is your comprehensive guide to the most prestigious celebration of extended reality excellence. This meticulously crafted document captures the essence of innovation, creativity, and technological advancement that defines the XR industry today.

From groundbreaking virtual reality experiences to cutting-edge augmented reality applications, the programme showcases the remarkable achievements of studios, developers, and visionaries who are pushing the boundaries of what's possible in immersive technology.

The programme serves as both a celebration of current achievements and a roadmap for the future of XR. It highlights the incredible diversity of applications across industries - from entertainment and gaming to healthcare, education, enterprise solutions, and beyond.

Each category represents a unique facet of the XR ecosystem, showcasing how different approaches to immersive technology can create meaningful, impactful experiences that resonate with users worldwide.

The anticipation surrounding this year's awards is palpable. The XR community has witnessed unprecedented growth and innovation, with new technologies, platforms, and creative approaches emerging at an incredible pace.

This year's programme reflects the maturity and sophistication that the XR industry has achieved, while still maintaining the pioneering spirit that has always defined this space.

The awards ceremony represents more than just recognition - it's a celebration of the collective effort, creativity, and determination that drives the XR industry forward. It's a moment to honor not just the winners, but every participant who has contributed to advancing the field of extended reality.

The programme will be available for viewing on the night of the awards, providing attendees and viewers with a comprehensive overview of all nominees, categories, and the incredible work being recognized.

This carefully curated collection represents the pinnacle of XR achievement, showcasing projects that have not only met but exceeded the highest standards of innovation, technical excellence, and user experience.

From immersive storytelling experiences that transport users to new worlds, to practical applications that solve real-world problems, the programme demonstrates the incredible versatility and potential of XR technology.

The awards recognize excellence across multiple dimensions - technical innovation, creative vision, user experience design, and real-world impact. Each nominee represents a unique approach to harnessing the power of immersive technology.

The programme also highlights the collaborative nature of the XR industry, showcasing how different disciplines come together to create experiences that are greater than the sum of their parts.

From concept to execution, each project featured in the programme represents countless hours of dedication, innovation, and passion from teams around the world.

The XR Awards Programme is more than just a document - it's a testament to the incredible talent, creativity, and vision that defines the extended reality community.

As we look forward to the awards ceremony, the programme serves as a reminder of how far the XR industry has come and the exciting possibilities that lie ahead.

The future of XR is being written today, and the projects featured in this programme are leading the way forward.

`;

const wordCount = articleContent.trim().split(/\s+/).filter(word => word.length > 0).length;
const readingTime = Math.ceil(wordCount / 250);
